children.subject: 1 semester of java/python at cc. We covered objects, classes, inheritance, polymorphism, data abstraction, constructors, and some gui apps. In python, we covered everything up to recursion in the equivalent of 61A.

Yea sounds like you’ll be fine without 61a! You might not be used to the rigor, however, it’s a big jump from CC classes. I took an advanced programming in java course at CC and 61b was ~3-4c harder. 61b doesn’t heavily rely on 61a.

I don't recommend 61b and 61c concurrently unless you somehow don't take anything else (or are already super confident with the matieral) - both classes are a HUGE time suck because they are heavily project based, each the projects require a ton of time 

(for perspective, I took 61b with Hilfinger Fall 2017 and would regularly spend about 30-40 hours on each project, and that was with a decent grasp of the matieral).
